# adigator-generated derivative files (forward / reverse / J'·v) + their data.
# These are produced next to the source by adigatorGen*; never commit them.
*_ADiGator*.m
*_ADiGator*.mat
*_Jac.m
*_Hes.m
*_Grd.m
*_RGrd.m
*_JtV.m
*_RGrd.mat
*_JtV.mat
adigatortempfunc*.m

# MATLAB Coder / build output (codegen examples, SCodegenTest, R15 codegen-equiv).
codegen/
codegen_lib/
slprj/
*_mex.*
*.mexa64
*.mexw64
*.mexmaca64
*.mexmaci64

# Editor / MATLAB autosave cruft.
*.asv

# Per-example scratch dirs for adigator-generated example output (issue #67/#69).
examples/**/generated/

# Proprietary bug reports (GMV source snippets) — NEVER commit, at ANY path.
# docs/analyses/.gitignore (a whitelist) is the primary guard for the current
# location; these path-INDEPENDENT rules are the belt-and-suspenders that survive
# folder renames — the 2026-07-05 docs/known-bugs → docs/analyses reorg removed
# the per-folder ignore and briefly un-ignored the report on a rebased branch.
# Do NOT whitelist these; the one PUBLIC review lives (and is whitelisted) at
# docs/analyses/2026-07-04-code-quality-review.md.
**/known-bugs/
**/adigator-bugs.md
**/*embedded-field-report*.md

# Intentional, committed generated-shaped fixtures (synthetic + offline-test
# fixtures): keep them — and any future ones — trackable without `git add -f`.
# Must stay last so it overrides the suffix rules above.
!tests/fixtures/**
